SIMPLE: posse_comitatus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Posse comitatus
<hw>Pos"se com`i*ta"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>posse</ets>
to be able, to have power + LL. <ets>comitatus</ets> a county, from
<ets>comes</ets>, <ets>comitis</ets>, a count. See <er>County</er>, and
<er>Power</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The power of the county, or the
citizens who may be summoned by the sheriff to assist the authorities in
suppressing a riot, or executing any legal precept which is forcibly
opposed.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection of people; a throng; a rabble.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The word <xex>comitatus</xex> is often omitted, and
<xex>posse</xex> alone used. ⟦ldquo⟧A whole <xex>posse</xex> of
enthusiasts.⟦rdquo⟧</note> <rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if the passion that rules were the sheriff of the place, and
came off with all the <qex>posse</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Possess</ent>⟦br⟧
